The paper deals with the problem of measuring the compressibility of repetitive sequences, which is a topic closely related to data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also introduces a new measure of repetitiveness based on attractors, which is a concept that has connections to computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses the size of context-free grammars, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG).
